### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Create a new location (using ENTITY property names)
POST {{baseUrl}}/location
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "LocationName": "chuka",
  "Address": "4060, chuka",
  "ContactNumber": "555-0101"
}

### 2. Create another location
POST {{baseUrl}}/location
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "LocationName": "Airport Branch",
  "Address": "456 Airport Road, Airport Zone, City",
  "ContactNumber": "555-0202"
}

### 3. Create location without contact number (nullable)
POST {{baseUrl}}/location
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "LocationName": "Mall Branch",
  "Address": "789 Shopping Mall, Retail District, City"
}

### 4. Get all locations
GET {{baseUrl}}/location

### 5. Get location by ID (replace {id} with actual location ID from response above)
GET {{baseUrl}}/location/1

### 6. Update location (replace {id} with actual location ID)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/location/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ContactNumber": "555-9999",
  "Address": "123 Updated Main Street, Downtown, City"
}

### 7. Search locations by name
GET {{baseUrl}}/location/search/Downtown

### 8. Find locations by name
GET {{baseUrl}}/location/name/Airport%20Branch

### 9. Find locations by address
GET {{baseUrl}}/location/address/Main

### 10. Delete a location (replace {id} with actual location ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/location/1